  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0d82\u0d9c\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The fourth wave in Bangladesh is severe",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Bangladesh is facing the fourth wave of Corona, and the country's health departments have expressed fear that this fourth wave of Corona has taken a terrible form.",
        "According to Bangladesh health authorities, the country's fourth wave of 'Covid 19' started on July 1. It is also reported that the country's hospitals are currently overflowing with new 'Covid-19' patients.",
        "It is said that the number of 'Covid 19' deaths reported within the last 5 days is 32. The number of reported deaths has crossed 2,500. It is also said that the number of 'Covid 19' infected people reported daily within the last 5 days is close to 50.",
        "Bangladesh health authorities have discovered that the cause of this new corona wave is 'BA5', a sub-variety of the 'Covid 19 Omicron' mutation."
      ],
